notes: The 7th wicket partnership of 119 by AO Suji and Odoyo is a new world record for one-day internationals. (Previous 7th wicket records: 115, PJL Dujon and MD Marshall, WI v Pak at Gujranwala, 1986/87 and AC Parore and LK Germon, 115 NZ v Pak at Sharjah, 1996/97.).

milestones.description: Thomas Odoyo and Tony Suji's 119-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 44 between Hitesh Modi and Thomas Odoyo
Chudasama has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (13) for KENYA, going past Aasif Karim
Thomas Odoyo and Tony Suji's 119-run partnership is the highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 115 between Marshall and Jeff Dujon
